# CI after push (blocking)

**A push is not done until required workflows are green** on that branch. Do not end the
session, open a PR as ready, or mark work complete after `git push` without watching.

## Workflows (by branch)

| Branch | Workflows | Must pass |
|--------|-----------|-----------|
| Any (`main`, `feat/**`, PRs) | `.github/workflows/ci.yml` | `python`, `frontend` (matrix) |
| **`main` only** | `.github/workflows/deploy-preflight.yml` | `build-smoke`; `modal-secrets` if repo secrets set |

**Common mistake:** Watching only `ci.yml` while `deploy-preflight` stays red on `main`.
That workflow runs on every `main` push (Modal import smoke + optional secrets check).

**CD (not a push gate):** `.github/workflows/deploy-modal.yml` is **continuous deployment**,
not a pre-merge check. It triggers via `workflow_run` after **CI succeeds on `main`**, then
re-runs build-smoke + secrets and `modal deploy`s the three Modal apps (embedding,
data-management, llm). Do not treat it as a "must pass before PR" gate; after a `main` merge,
confirm it deployed (or was correctly skipped without Modal secrets). DigitalOcean apps
auto-deploy separately via `deploy_on_push: true` in `infra/do/*.yaml`.

## After every push (required)

```bash
# From repo root; branch defaults to current
bash scripts/ci/watch_github_ci.sh [branch]
```

The script waits for a run on **`origin/<branch>` HEAD** for each required workflow, then
`gh run watch` until success. On `main` it watches **both** `ci.yml` and `deploy-preflight.yml`.

Manual equivalent:

```bash
BRANCH=main
SHA=$(git rev-parse origin/$BRANCH)
for wf in ci.yml deploy-preflight.yml; do
  gh run list --branch "$BRANCH" --workflow "$wf" --json databaseId,headSha,conclusion \
    | jq --arg sha "$SHA" 'first(.[] | select(.headSha == $sha))'
done
```

| Outcome | Action |
|---------|--------|
| **success** (all required workflows) | Record run URLs; proceed |
| **failure** | `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed` → fix → push again → re-watch |
| **cancelled** (0 jobs on preflight) | Another push superseded this run — finish watch before pushing again |
| **User waives** | AskQuestion only; note waiver in PR/summary |

## Before the first push (local parity)

When changes touch Python, frontends, workflows, Modal, or secrets:

```bash
uv sync --group dev
bash scripts/check_modal_no_database_url.sh
bash scripts/check_openapi_specs.sh
bash scripts/check_secrets.sh
bash scripts/check_no_operator_specs_tracked.sh
uv run ruff check apps packages tests
uv run ruff format --check apps packages tests
uv run basedpyright apps packages tests
uv run pytest tests/unit tests/integration tests/privacy tests/e2e tests/smoke tests/eval
cd apps/chat-rag-frontend && npm ci && npm run lint && npm test
cd apps/data-management-frontend && npm ci && npm run lint && npm test
```

**Before push to `main`** (matches deploy-preflight `build-smoke` job):

```bash
bash scripts/deploy/verify_build.sh
```

## After merge to `main`

Watch **CI + deploy preflight** on `main` for the merge commit (H0ci / 15-service-health):

```bash
bash scripts/ci/watch_github_ci.sh main
```

If `main` is red after your merge, fix in the same session before declaring deploy/health **PASS**.

## Do not

- Report "CI green" after watching only `ci.yml` on a **`main`** push.
- Chain multiple `git push` commands to `main` without waiting — deploy-preflight used to
  cancel prior runs and show false failures in the Actions UI.
- Mark hotfix **resolved**, milestone **complete**, or PR **ready to merge** while any
  required workflow is red on that branch.

